cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.HC 

The paper deals with the detection of endoscopic artifacts in video frames, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques for artifact detection, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.LG (Machine Learning), or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of improving patient care, which could make it relevant to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
